# RDF 2.0.0 Release Notes

## What's New
- Canonical-first architecture — all content is tool-agnostic markdown
- {domain}-{role} naming convention across all agents and commands
- Unified 'rdf' CLI replacing install.sh/sync.sh
- 4-profile system: core, systems-engineering, security, frontend
- GitHub Issues + Projects v2 as durable work tracking layer
- Self-verification gates in QA and Sentinel (addresses false-positive friction)
- Scope confirmation in EM/mgr (addresses wrong-scope friction)
- Deterministic state helper (rdf state) for context anchoring

## Breaking Changes
- workforce/ directory renamed to rdf/
- All agent CC names changed (rfxn-se -> rfxn-sys-eng, etc.)
- All persona slash commands changed (/se -> /sys-eng, etc.)
- /root/.claude/ is now a deployment target — develop in rdf/canonical/

## Migration
Run `rdf generate claude-code` then symlink output to /root/.claude/.
See README.md for full migration instructions.
